sql:
SELECT severity
FROM anomalies
ORDER BY severity DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'Critical issues' refer to anomalies with 'Medium' or 'High' severity levels; 
- 'Detection time' is the timestamp when the anomaly was recorded; 
- 'Sensor information' includes the sensor type and its location; 
- 'Last service date' refers to when the aircraft component was last serviced; 
- 'User edits' imply any 'edit' actions logged within an hour after the anomaly detection.
